  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6767 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6770 (-13.3B) and positive gamma at 6780 (+8.9B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy any dip toward 6765-6770 and sell any rally toward 6780-6800. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma overall, creating a powerful mean-reversion setup with extreme sensitivity around current levels given the concentrated negative gamma just above spot. The gex_surge event combined with the -86.7% 1-minute change suggests dealers just executed significant hedging flows, likely buying into weakness given proximity to the 6770 amplifying level.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect tight, choppy trading between 6765-6780 with strong support below and resistance above.",
